Serializable, Comparable<Month>
public enum Month
extends Enum<Month>

This enumerates the months in the gregorian calendar and adds some extra functionality to each month.

getDays

public int getDays(int year)
Returns the number of days for this month in the given year. The year parameter is only applicable for february due to leap years.

Parameters:
year - The year to get the number of days for the month.
Returns:
Returns the number of days in the month.

getMonthOneBased

public static final Month getMonthOneBased(int month)
Returns the month for the given integer value. This is one based so that if the value passed in is 2, then February is returned.

Parameters:
month - The one based month to return.
Returns:
The month and never null.
Throws:
ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - If the month parameter is less than 1 or greater than 12.
